                                                <h3>A new luxury norm? – Chalhoub Group launches white paper to explore the evolving face of luxury in the Gulf</h3>
                                                <p class="Default">[London: 20 May 2016] Chalhoub Group, the leading partner for luxury across the Middle East, launches today the Group’s fourth white paper, ‘The Evolving Face Of Luxury In The Gulf: On Our Way To A New Norm?’.</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">Detailed knowledge of the Middle East and its people is at the forefront of Chalhoub Group’s business practices. With over 60 years of experience in the industry, the Group is the go-to partner for major international brands wanting to enter the Middle Eastern market; with extensive experience in building brands in the region across the beauty, fashion and gift sectors.</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">Following three decades of rapid and strong growth, luxury in the Gulf is going through a period of transition with shifts in the retail landscape and luxury consumers’ profiles, which will undoubtedly re-shape the outlook of the luxury marketplace in the coming years. Chalhoub Group’s fourth white paper sets out to address how the luxury market in the Middle East is evolving as it reaches a maturity phase, and introduce the concept of a <em>New Norm </em>– a new way of doing business to adapt to this changing luxury eco-system.</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">The <em>New Norm</em> for luxury in the Gulf looks beyond those geopolitical and economic challenges facing the region such as a prolonged period of low oil prices and exchange rate fluctuations; and goes deeper to understand the profound forces that are occurring within the Gulf luxury sector itself – to reveal a more mature face characterized by huge untapped potential.</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">The Group’s research in the Middle East has found that:</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <ul>
                                                    <li>The number of high-net-worth individuals in the region and their wealth is actually increasing, with numbers set to grow by 40% compared to 25% growth in Europe and North America by 2024; while a growing middle class and number of women in the workplace also represent an increasing pool of consumers with promising purchasing power</li>
                                                    <li>The business environment is more formally defined and framed by regulation addressing governance, labour laws and consumer protection</li>
                                                    <li>The region has one of the highest rates of luxury brand penetration in the world</li>
                                                    <li>The region is displaying a maturing retail environment in terms of expanding available retail space and the variety of shopping environments </li>
                                                    <li>The emergence of digital in the luxury retail sector in the Gulf means that traditional marketing and the conventional in-store retail experience are being upended</li>
                                                    <li>Luxury consumers are evolving and now seek more experiential-focused consumption; comparing prices, service quality and availability of the latest products </li>
                                                </ul>
                                                <p class="Default"><em>&nbsp;</em></p>
                                                <p class="Default">With this maturing phase underway, the role of local partner’s such as Chalhoub Group has become even more pronounced in terms of their ability to draw on their extensive experience in the Gulf to support international brands with their development, against a changing luxury backdrop.</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">The Group’s white paper identifies key attributes of today’s local partner in order to help brands adapt and thrive in the Middle East under the <em>New Norm</em>:</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <ul>
                                                    <li>Shares risks</li>
                                                    <li>Fosters operational efficiency through economies of scale and “plug and play” shared services</li>
                                                    <li>Applies its networks and knowledge of the region to help address the increased complexity of regulations and decision-making – for example, in order to ensure a smooth registration process, Chalhoub Group operates special compliance teams to prepare the required&nbsp; documentation and then follow-up with local authorities to ensure fast approval </li>
                                                    <li>Leverages its extensive customer experience to impart customer-centric, bespoke product offers and services – for example, Chalhoub Group’s Guest Experience Initiative, designed to take the luxury shopping experience to the next level</li>
                                                    <li>Nurtures innovation to create market-relevant and compelling shopping experiences – for example, Chalhoub Group’s unique concept store, Level Shoes in Dubai Mall, which delivers a revolutionary, immersive shoe experience across 9,600sqm </li>
                                                </ul>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">Patrick Chalhoub, Co-CEO Chalhoub Group, commented: The Gulf region has witnessed a period of abundance for the past 25 years with the building of incredible infrastructure and the development of the education of its young and vibrant population.</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">It is now entering a new phase of maturity, of knowledge, of seriousness and of stronger governance. Despite the immediate geopolitical and economic challenges, this is a region of wealth and of steady growth. To be successful, we will have to be aspirational, meaningful and competitive, and adapt to the changes and to the <em>New Norm.</em>”</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p class="Default">&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p><strong>Ends</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
