                                                <p>The aim of this strategy is to contribute to the long-term development of the Middle East through the Group’s dedicated resources. As the leading partner for luxury across the Middle East, the Chalhoub Group has decided to take the lead and act as a role model for the region to ensure a sustainable future for generations to come. This unique model has been tailor-made to the region’s needs. The Group believes that through education, we will be able to address societal, environmental and humanitarian issues. The Middle East is known to have the highest youth unemployment in the world. The Group empowers local youth regionally and internationally through capacity building (partnerships, scholarships and mentorships, entrepreneurship, etc.) reducing the gap between skillset and market demands.</p>
                                                <p>“<em>We are a family business driven by the values of respect, excellence and entrepreneurial spirit. We believe that sustainability is the balance between economic priorities, promoting empowerment for all stakeholders and environmental protection. This year, we are celebrating 60 years of building brands in the region and throughout our journey we have learned and we are convinced thatPress Releasesustainable business is in an opportunity to create value while making the world a better place</em>.” said Patrick Chalhoub, co-CEO of the Chalhoub Group.</p>
                                                <p>Environmental conservation is also a key issue addressed through the UN Global Compact, and as a member, the Chalhoub Group is expected to follow high standards of responsibility. The last half decade has seen unprecedented economic growth for the region, but with this has come an increased demand for energy and natural resources. The Chalhoub Group strives to reduce the environmental footprint through engagement, awareness and efficiency of operations.</p>
                                                <p>“<em>Our commitment to environmental sustainability continues to be driven by the engagement of our stakeholders through an education and awareness process. Several of the GCC countries contribute to the highest rate of greenhouse gas emissions per capita and fall within the scope of our regional operations. The key challenge is turning this trend around is a change of mind-set. We are obliged as a business operation in these countries to advocate for environmental protection.</em>” said Anthony Chalhoub, co-CEO of the Chalhoub Group.</p>
                                                <p>As part of their commitment and through this membership, the Chalhoub Group has promised to release an annual report sharing their sustainability performance. This report has received third party verification from the Global Reporting Initiative, a leading organisation in this field, promoting this way of reporting for organisations to become more concerned about the future.</p>
                                                <p>The Group has embarked on this journey of sustainability knowing the path is long and with many obstacles along the way.</p>
                                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p>ABOUT THE CHALHOUB GROUP</p>
                                                <p>The Chalhoub Group is the leading partner for luxury across the Middle East since 1955. As an expert in retail, distribution and marketing services based in Dubai, the Group has become a major player in the beauty, fashion and gift sectors regionally.</p>
                                                <p>By blending its Middle East expertise and intimate knowledge of luxury, the Chalhoub Group is building brands in the region, by offering service excellence to all its partners and a unique experience to its customers through its passionate teams.</p>
                                                <p>With a growing workforce of more than 11,000 people, implemented in 14 countries, as well as operating over 600 retail stores, the Group's success is attributed to its most valued asset: highly skilled and dedicated teams. Professionalism and passion are what fuel the Chalhoub Group's competitive edge in today's market.</p>
                                                <p>By being committed to implementing sustainable practices into their business, the Chalhoub Group was awarded in 2014, for the second consecutive year, the CSR Label from the Dubai Chamber of Commerce and has been accepted as a new member of the United Nations Global Compact Community.</p>
